e_config::ConfiguredTier::BestEffort => DeliveryTier::BestEffort,\n};\n```\n\n**Suggested simplification:** Implement `From<ConfiguredTier> for DeliveryTier` in `reme_config` or `reme_transport` (whichever owns the boundary), or add a local helper:\n\n```rust\nfn delivery_tier(tier: reme_config::ConfiguredTier) -> DeliveryTier {\n    match tier {\n        reme_config::ConfiguredTier::Quorum => DeliveryTier::Quorum,\n        reme_config::ConfiguredTier::BestEffort => DeliveryTier::BestEffort,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThen both call sites become `delivery_tier(parsed_peer.common.tier)`.\n\n**Why it is better:** If a new tier variant is added, only one place needs updating. The `From` impl approach is idiomatic Rust and would benefit other consumers too.\n\n---\n\n#### Finding 7: The LAN discovery block's deep nesting hurts readability\n\n**File:** `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`, lines 688-753\n\nThe discovery initialization block is nested 4 levels deep: `if enabled` -> `match MdnsSdBackend::new()` -> `Ok(backend)` -> `if allow_direct_lan`. Combined with the advertising block inside, the deepest code is at 5 indentation levels.\n\n**Suggested simplification:** Extract the entire block into a standalone function in `discovery/mod.rs`:\n\n```rust\npub async fn initialize(\n    config: &LanDiscoveryConfig,\n    http_bind: Option<&str>,\n    identity: &Identity,\n    storage: &Storage,\n    coordinator: &Arc<TransportCoordinator>,\n) -> Option<DiscoveryState> { ... }\n```\n\nThis moves approximately 65 lines out of the already-long `App::new()` (which has the `#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]` annotation). The `App::new()` call site becomes:\n\n```rust\nlet discovery = discovery::initialize(\n    &config.lan_discovery, config.embedded_node.http_bind.as_deref(),\n    &identity, &storage, &coordinator,\n).await;\n```\n\n**Why it is better:**\n- Reduces `App::new()` length (the annotation at line 371 acknowledges it is too long).\n- The discovery initialization is self-contained with clear inputs and a single output.\n- Easier to test in isolation.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| # | Area | Severity | Effort |\n|---|------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | Triple-Option -> `DiscoveryState` struct | Medium | Low |\n| 2 | Port parsing via `SocketAddr` | Low (correctness) | Trivial |\n| 3 | Reuse `our_routing_key` | Low | Trivial |\n| 4 | Simplify `shutdown_discovery` (follows from 1) | Medium | Low |\n| 5 | Extract priority clamping helper | Low | Trivial |\n| 6 | Extract tier conversion helper or `From` impl | Low | Trivial |\n| 7 | Extract discovery init to `discovery::initialize()` | Medium | Medium |\n\nFindings 1, 4, and 7 are the highest-leverage changes. Finding 1 eliminates impossible states at the type level. Finding 7 directly addresses the `too_many_lines` annotation on `App::new()`. Finding 2 is a minor correctness improvement that prevents potential IPv6 edge cases.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>40259</total_tokens><tool_uses>10</tool_uses><duration_ms>116740</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/36b495c0-95b9-49fc-8523-b911e74011a9/tasks/a00b63038759a537d.output",
