(Runtime Integration) | ~75% | No TUI peer state, no TUI mDNS notification, contact snapshot is static |\n| **Chunk 5** (Channel Binding) | 0% | Intentionally deferred (documented in threat model) |\n| **Chunk 8** (Docs) | ~30% | Threat model exists but config examples, known limitations docs missing |\n\n---\n\n## Cross-cutting Observations\n\n1. **Plan vs threat model disagreement on channel binding** — Plan Chunk 5 lists it as work to do; threat model says it was \"rejected.\" Need reconciliation.\n2. **WHITEPAPER Section 11.6 is stale** — shows `node_pubkey, routing_keys, signature` in response but implementation returns only `signature` (for privacy). Whitepaper should be updated.\n3. **All 385+ tests pass** — the implementation is functionally solid for what it covers.\n4. **No integration tests for the discovery async event loop** — only synchronous unit tests exist for the controller.\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Agent Reports\n\n### Area 1: Discovery Crate (`crates/reme-discovery/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Critical:**\n\n- **C1 — `unregister()`/`shutdown()` receivers dropped** (`mdns_sd.rs:192-194`, `222-224`): `mdns_sd::ServiceDaemon::unregister()` returns `Result<Receiver<UnregisterStatus>>`. The code calls `.map_err(...)` on the outer `Result` and drops the receiver, so unregistration is dispatched but never confirmed. `stop_advertising()` can return `Ok(())` while the service is still advertised. Same for `shutdown()` which returns `Result<Receiver<DaemonStatus>>`.\n\n- **C2 — Browse thread `JoinHandle` not stored** (`mdns_sd.rs:94-123`): The browse thread spawned by `ensure_browsing()` exits only when `browse_receiver.recv()` returns `Err`. `shutdown()` calls `daemon.shutdown()` but cannot join the thread. No guarantee the thread has exited when `shutdown()` returns. `state.browsing` is never reset to `false`.\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **M1 — TOCTOU in `start_advertising()`** (`mdns_sd.rs:129-178`): Lock dropped between Phase 1 (check) and Phase 3 (commit). Concurrent calls can both pass the check and register, orphaning the first registration.\n\n- **M2 — `Mutex` held across `daemon.browse()`** (`mdns_sd.rs:76-124`): `ensure_browsing()` acquires `self.state.lock()` then calls `self.daemon.browse()` while holding it. `daemon.browse()` sends to an internal channel which could block if full.\n\n- **Version check rejects v!=1 with no forward-compat** (`txt.rs:69-71`): `decode_txt` hard-rejects any version other than 1. `encode_txt` accepts any `version: u8` — asymmetric API.\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- Fake backend tests (`fake.rs:99-198`): 5 of 6 tests are `#[tokio::test] async fn` with no `.await`.\n- Channel capacity mismatch: fake=64 (`fake.rs:21`), real=128 (`mdns_sd.rs:39`).\n- `RawDiscoveredPeer` and `DiscoveryEvent` don't derive `PartialEq` — forces pattern-match in tests.\n- `DiscoveryError` missing `#[non_exhaustive]`.\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**Major deviations:**\n\n- **M3 — Hex vs base64url**: Plan says `rk=<routing_key_base64url>`, implementation uses `hex::encode`. Wire-format mismatch.\n- **M4 — Missing TXT fields**: Plan specifies `relay=1` and `identity=1`. Neither encoded nor decoded. `relay` is arguably v0.6 scope, but `identity` is v0.4.\n- Extra `port` TXT field not in the discovery contract (harmless but deviates).\n- **M5 — No test for `v=2`**: Unknown-but-valid version path untested.\n\n**Minor deviations:**\n\n- **m4 — No `bind_interfaces`**: `MdnsSdBackend::new()` takes no parameters. Plan requires interface filter.\n- No `DiscoveryService` type (plan lists it, functionality covered by trait+backends).\n\n**Compliant:** Crate dependency constraint (no reme-transport/reme-identity), service type `_reme._tcp.local.`, event types, fake backend, feature gating.\n\n#### Simplifier\n\nTop findings:\n- TOCTOU in `start_advertising` three-phase lock (High impact)\n- `ensure_browsing` silently swallows failures — dead receiver (Medium)\n- `decode_txt` bare tuple return → named struct (Medium)\n- Divergent channel capacities → shared constant (Medium)\n- Missing `PartialEq` derives on types → simpler tests (Low)\n\n---\n\n### Area 2: Transport Capabilities (`crates/reme-transport/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **M6 — MQTT quorum path** (`coordinator.rs:663-676`): HTTP targets correctly filtered by `targets_where(|c| c.quorum_credit)`. MQTT uses `pool.all_targets()` — no capability filter. `quorum_target_count`/`quorum_target_ids` DO filter MQTT, creating an inconsistency between the count and the actual delivery set.\n\n- **`replace_target()` upsert semantics** (`pool.rs:143-150`): Always inserts `new_target` even if `old_id` not found. Pool doc says \"replacement\" but behavior is upsert. Coordinator doc correctly describes upsert.\n\n- **`fetch_from_targets` layered filter** (`pool.rs:623-659`): `fetch_once` falls back to `all_targets()`, then `fetch_from_targets` re-filters by capability. Correct but fragile — a fast-path optimization could bypass the filter.\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- `subscribe()` silently returns empty channel when no HTTP pool configured.\n- `TargetConfig` struct literal syntax breaks with new `capabilities` field (acceptable for prototype stage).\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**High deviations:**\n\n- **M7 — `TransportRegistry` still has mutation methods**: Plan requires read-only conversion. `add_http_target()` and other mutators still present. Dual write authority.\n- **M8 — `MessageReceiver` not deprecated**: Still exported, no `#[deprecated]` attribute.\n\n**Medium deviations:**\n\n- **m7 — `stable_defaults()` has `replicate: false`**: Plan says all flags set for stable. No enforcement points exist for `replicate` yet.\n- `update_http_target` became `replace_http_target` — different name/signature but improved semantics.\n\n**Compliant:** `fetch_once` filters by FETCH, `submit_to_quorum_targets` filters by QUORUM_CREDIT, invariant tests present, booleans vs bitflags documented.\n\n#### Simplifier\n\nTop findings:\n- Derive `Default` on `TargetCapabilities` (Medium)\n- `quorum_target_count` via `quorum_target_ids().len()` — eliminate duplication (Medium)\n- Rename `targets_where` → `targets_by_capability` (Low)\n- Consistent delegation style in coordinator mutations (Low)\n- Doc comments reference bitflag-style names but implementation uses booleans (Low)\n\n---\n\n### Area 3: Discovery Controller (`apps/client/src/discovery/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Critical:**\n\n- **C3 — SEC-2 timing oracle** (`controller.rs:362-367`): `verify_peer_identity` returns on first matching candidate. Plan requires iterating all N candidates with constant-time final decision.\n\n- **C4 — SEC-3 channel binding missing** (`controller.rs:324-369`): `build_identity_sign_data` signs `\"reme-identity-v1:\" || challenge || node_pubkey`. No responder IP:port. MITM can relay challenge to real peer. No FIXME at call site.\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **`TargetId` constructed independently** (`controller.rs:240-260`): `PeerEntry.target_id` computed with `TargetId::http(url)` separately from the `HttpTarget`'s internal ID. Forward fragility if URL construction diverges.\n\n- **URL-unchanged short-circuit** (`controller.rs:157-169`): Skips re-verification when URL unchanged. No safety net — periodic refresh and stale-peer lifecycle not implemented.\n\n- **`expect()` in constructor** (`controller.rs:108`): `reqwest::Client::builder().build().expect(...)` panics inside a spawned task — silent crash.\n\n- **`max_peers=0` silently clamped** (`controller.rs:94`): No warning logged.\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- Shutdown uses `iter` + `clear()` instead of `drain()`.\n- `LanDiscoveryConfig` has no `max_peers > 0` validation.\n- Contact index collision test is artificial (same routing key assigned manually).\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**Major deviations:**\n\n- **M9 — No periodic refresh**: No timer, no `tokio::time::interval`. `refresh_interval_secs` config field missing entirely.\n- **M10 — No stale-peer lifecycle**: No Suspended state, no failure counter, no `stale_timeout`.\n- **M11 — No `verified_peer_index`**: Controller uses `peer_index: HashMap<String, PeerEntry>` keyed by instance name. No `HashMap<PublicID, Vec<TargetId>>` for multi-device support.\n\n**Minor deviations:**\n\n- **m11 — Config name**: `allow_direct_lan` vs plan's `auto_direct_known_contacts`.\n- SEC-2 timing safety: short-circuits on first match (reiterated from code review).\n\n**Compliant:** Event subscription, rk matching, HTTP skip on zero matches, target add/remove via coordinator, 256 peer cap, `enabled` default false.\n\n#### Simplifier\n\nTop findings:\n- Remove `target_id` from `PeerEntry` — compute on the fly (Medium)\n- Collapse `verified`/`working_url` into single `Option<(PublicID, String)>` (Low)\n- Add `debug!` logging to base64/signature-length failures (Low)\n- Rename `default_true` → `default_allow_direct_lan` (Low)\n\n---\n\n### Area 4: Client Runtime Integration (`apps/client/src/tui/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **M12 — Static contact snapshot** (`app.rs:696-707`): `storage.list_contacts()` called once at startup. Contacts added at runtime invisible to discovery controller until restart.\n\n- **Coordinator polling cancellation ordering** (`app.rs:330, 936-942`): `_coordinator_handle` drops after async shutdown, accumulating unread events during shutdown. Should cancel explicitly first.\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- **m14 — Port extraction** (`app.rs:724-728`): `rsplit(':').next()` silently falls back to 23004. Should use `SocketAddr::parse` or `listener.local_addr()`.\n- Orphan `CancellationToken` when `allow_direct_lan = false`.\n- `unwrap_or_else` on `storage.list_contacts()` degrades silently (acceptable with `warn!`).\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**Major deviations:**\n\n- **M13 — No TUI-visible discovered-peer state**: Zero UI references to \"discover\" or \"mDNS\". Users cannot see LAN peers.\n- **M14 — No TUI notification when mDNS inactive**: `warn!` logged to file but no UI indicator.\n- **M7 (reiterated) — TransportRegistry still has mutation methods**.\n\n**Minor deviations:**\n\n- **m13 — `send_text()` not migrated to `send_text_tiered()`**: Delivery phase not surfaced in UI.\n- `MessageReceiver` not deprecated (reiterated).\n- `direct_peers` missing deprecation warning for entries without `public_id`.\n\n**Compliant:** Client type migration, EDGE-6 graceful degradation, EDGE-3 advertise-after-bind, background browse, controller spawn, configured peers preserved, disabled-feature isolation.\n\n#### Simplifier\n\nTop findings:\n- **S1 — Triple-Option → `DiscoveryState` struct** (Medium, eliminates impossible states)\n- **S2 — Extract discovery init to `discovery::initialize()`** (Medium, reduces `App::new` length)\n- Port parsing via `SocketAddr` (Low)\n- Priority clamping helper — DRY (Low)\n- `ConfiguredTier` → `DeliveryTier` conversion — `From` impl (Low)\n\n---\n\n### Area 5: Node + Docs (`apps/node/`, `docs/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **m15 — `sign_data` not zeroized** (`api.rs:919-925`): `generate_receipt` zeroizes `sign_data`; `get_identity` does not. Inconsistent security practice.\n- **m16 — Threat model references `MAX_PEERS`** (`threat-model.md:48`): Constant no longer exists. Should reference `LanDiscoveryConfig.max_peers`.\n- Module-level doc comment in `api.rs` is stale (omits identity/health endpoints).\n- Threat model §2 understates information leak (contact-graph edge not mentioned).\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- `DefaultBodyLimit` only on `auth_routes` — public routes have no explicit cap (fine for GET-only).\n- AGENTS.md `unwrap()` ban covers library crates only — apps use `expect()` correctly.\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**Deviations:**\n\n- **Channel binding rejected in threat model but listed as Chunk 5 work in plan** — disagreement.\n- **WHITEPAPER 11.6 stale** — response format shows `node_pubkey, routing_keys, signature` but implementation returns only `signature`.\n- Threat model missing SEC-2 and SEC-5 documentation.\n- Chunk 8 (docs) not yet implemented — expected per dependency