            "content": "# Fix Plan: `feat/lan-discovery` Review Findings\n\n## Context\n\nThe review of `feat/lan-discovery` against `master` produced 4 critical, 14 major, 16 minor findings and 7 simplification opportunities. This plan addresses everything actionable. Work is decomposed into independent units suitable for parallel subagent execution with worktree isolation.\n\n## Implementation Strategy\n\nUse `superpowers:subagent-driven-development` with `isolation: \"worktree\"` for each unit. Units are independent — each touches a distinct file set. After all units land, run `cargo test --workspace` and `cargo clippy --workspace` as final verification.\n\n**Branch strategy:** Create `fix/lan-discovery-review` from current `feat/lan-discovery` HEAD. Each subagent works in its own worktree, commits to its own branch, and opens a PR against `feat/lan-discovery`.\n\n---\n\n## Unit 1: mDNS Backend Correctness (C1, C2, M1, M2, m5)\n\n**Files:** `crates/reme-discovery/src/mdns_sd.rs`, `crates/reme-discovery/src/types.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **C1 — Await unregister/shutdown receivers:** `daemon.unregister()` returns `Result<Receiver<UnregisterStatus>>`. Receive from it to confirm completion. Same for `daemon.shutdown()` which returns `Result<Receiver<DaemonStatus>>`. Use `tokio::task::spawn_blocking` for the blocking recv since these are async methods.\n\n2. **C2 — Store browse thread JoinHandle:** Add `browse_handle: Option<std::thread::JoinHandle<()>>` to `MdnsState`. In `shutdown()`, join the handle after calling `daemon.shutdown()`. Reset `browsing = false` in shutdown.\n\n3. **M1 — Fix TOCTOU in `start_advertising`:** Hold the `Mutex` through the entire operation. The Phase 2 work (hostname lookup, ServiceInfo::new, daemon.register) is fast in-process work, not blocking I/O. Remove the three-phase pattern.\n\n4. **M2 — Narrow lock scope in `ensure_browsing`:** Drop the lock before calling `daemon.browse()`. Set `browsing = true` before dropping (claiming the slo